10:07 AM Attorney David R. Knaapen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Robert A. Gardner in court for Seann CPD Vancleve.   State requests warrant.  Court reviews that there was a call to their office.  Attorney Gardner also received a call from a family member.  Court orders warrant, body only will hold off signing for 24 hours.

10:47 AM Prosecuting attorney David R. Knaapen in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Seann CPD Vancleve in court. Attorney Robert Gardner in court.
Allie Eckes is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Knaapen. She is a police officer with the Marshfield Police Department. On 3/23/22, she performed a traffic stop. The defendant was identified as the driver of the vehicle. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. She suspected that the defendant was impaired and attempted to have him field sobriety tests. He refused to get out of the vehicle. She testifies as to the efforts to get the defendant out of the vehicle. The window had to be broke. She and other officers were dressed in police uniform. They were eventually able to get the door open, but defendant continued to refuse to get out of the vehicle. They had to use force to get him out of the vehicle. Officer Larson sustained a hand injury that he had to seek medical attention for. Attorney Gardner cross-examines witness.  
Attorney Gardner makes statement and moves to dismiss felony.
Attorney Knaapen makes statement.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Bond is continued.
Arraignment scheduled for April 18, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on March 29, 2022 at 10:45 am.
